.TH SDL_realloc_func 3type "SDL 3.1.3" "Simple Directmedia Layer" "SDL3 DATATYPES"
.SH NAME
SDL_realloc_func \- A callback used to implement 
.BR SDL_realloc
()\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_stdinc\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "typedef void *(SDLCALL *SDL_realloc_func)(void *mem, size_t size);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
SDL will always ensure that the passed
.BR size
is greater than 0\[char46]

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I mem
a pointer to allocated memory to reallocate, or NULL\[char46]
.TP
.I size
the new size of the memory\[char46]
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns a pointer to the newly allocated memory, or NULL if allocation
failed\[char46]

.SH THREAD SAFETY
It should be safe to call this callback from any thread\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This datatype is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

